-align: -webkit-left; text-indent: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration: none;\">Class work: <span class=\"instructure_file_holder link_holder instructure_file_link_holder\"><a class=\"inline_disabled preview_in_overlay\" title=\"Fnce3030 Nov 6.pdf\" href=\"https://canvas.colorado.edu/courses/123249/files/81588393?wrap=1\" target=\"_blank\" data-canvas-previewable=\"false\" data-api-endpoint=\"https://canvas.colorado.edu/api/v1/courses/123249/files/81588393\" data-api-returntype=\"File\">Fnce3030 Nov 6.pdf</a><a class=\"file_download_btn\" role=\"button\" download=\"\" style=\"margin-inline-start: 5px; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"https://canvas.colorado.edu/courses/123249/files/81588393/download?download_frd=1\"><span role=\"presentation\"><svg viewBox=\"0 0 1920 1920\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" style=\"width:1em; height:1em; vertical-align:middle; fill:currentColor\">\n    <path d=\"m1807.093 1482.477 79.736 79.963-355.313 355.312H355.346L.035 1562.44l79.85-79.963 322.22 322.334H1484.76l322.334-322.334ZM997.677-.033v1167.02l355.313-355.313 79.962 79.85-491.858 491.633L449.46 891.524l79.962-79.85 355.313 355.313V-.033h112.941Z\" fill-rule=\"evenodd\"></path>\n</svg>\n</span><span class=\"screenreader-only\">Download Fnce3030 Nov 6.pdf</span></a></span></div>\n  \n  \n<div id=\"assign-to-mount-point\"></div>\n<div id=\"choose-editor-mount-point\"></div>",
	"contentText": "Week 12\n  \n  \n  \n    Overview\n\n\n\n\nConcept of equilibrium in capital markets, the capital asset pricing model, single-factor index models, idiosyncratic risk, market beta and alpha, the arbitrage pricing theory, multi-factor models of risk and returns \n \n\n\n\n\nLearning Objectives\nUpon completion of this week, you will be able to understand:\n\nhow capital markets equilibrium constraint the relationship between risk and risk premium\nthe main implication of the capital asset pricing model (CAPM)\nthe distinction between absolute, market and idiosyncratic risk\nhow to use index models to calculate market betas and alphas\nthe limitations of the CAPM model and the role of other theories\nthe implications of the Arbitrage Pricing Theory\nthe multi-factor models of risk and return\nwhether these asset pricing theories are supported by the data\n\n \nPreparation for class\nMandatory reading:\nLecture 5: lecture 5.pdf\n    \n\nDownload lecture 5.pdf\nData support: TreynorBlack Data Work.xlsx\n    \n\nDownload TreynorBlack Data Work.xlsx\n \nLecture 6:lecture 6.pdf\n    \n\nDownload lecture 6.pdf \nData support: FF25PlusFF3.xlsx\n    \n\nDownload FF25PlusFF3.xlsx\n \nClass\nClass zoom link: Class logistics\n \n \nAssignments and Quizzes\nIB A1\nA5\n \nAdditional Resources\nChapters 9 and 10\n \nClass Notes\nNov 4 class recording: \nhttps://cuboulder.zoom.us/rec/share/ppq68QQ2F-hV6-10_aFgewYPC5Dn-x_c46j8IHJ8Mz2x9lCE5xxVfT94PtmxQspk.NbUN0A0hQzTbAeyc\n    \n\nLinks to an external site.\nPasscode: d1G8?Nhj\nClass work: TreynorBlack Data Work 008.xlsx\n    \n\nDownload TreynorBlack Data Work 008.xlsx\n \n \nNov 6 class recording: \nhttps://cuboulder.zoom.us/rec/share/tlqXHWg86n68_1Gd0wHV3oWp6EDAvFqP-eubmwG82gtxFPyceqlhAGfu_6XODtg.b2MYmLoN8UMFSOX0 \n    \n\nLinks to an external site.\nPasscode: 9Q?AxW4?\nClass work: Fnce3030 Nov 6.pdf\n    \n\nDownload Fnce3030 Nov 6.pdf\n  \n  \n\n",
